If that &quot;bedroom&quot; full of bunk beds looks more like a dormitory, it's because the Arcadia was a flophouse -- referred to in reports as a &quot;lodging house&quot; --  not a hotel.

From an online record of historic American fire tragedies:
&quot;1913 [Boston] -- December 3rd, a fire raced through the Arcadia Lodging House at 1202 Washington Street. The Boston Fire Department was credited with saving many lives. Even with the heroic efforts of the BFD, 28 men died and 20 were injured. Some of the fatalities had jumped from the upper floors.&quot;
